Which of the following can be used for assignment in R? #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:10022022123038]

Correct Ans: All of the above. In R, There are three different assignment operators: two of them have leftwards and rightwards forms. The operators `<-` and `=` assign into the environment in which they are evaluated. The operators #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:10022022220006]

`<<-` and `->>` are normally only used in functions, and cause a search to be made through parent environments for an existing definition of the variable being assigned. If such a variable is found (and its binding is not locked) #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:10022022220006]
then its value is redefined, otherwise assignment takes place in the global environment. #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:10022022220006]
